The keyword 'var' is a function scope VAR meaning that it can be used anywhere within the function. 'let', however is block scoped meaning that it can only be used within the block that it is defined. 
Ex: Using var
	function alpha() {
		var x = 25; 
		console.log(x); //=> 25
		x += 5; 
		console.log(x); //=> 30
	}
Ex: Using let
	function alpha() {
		var x = 25; 
		if (x === 25) {
			let y = 5; // VAR y can only be used within this block
			console.log(x + y); //=> 30
		}
		console.log(x + y); //=> error
		// VAR y cannot be used here
	}

